source.name: Baby Names: Top Names by Year
source.description:
The column chart shows the top baby first names by year. The chart can be filtered by year, gender, and count by changing these options under the Filter tab. The default filter settings show the top ten baby name. To view more or less than the top ten, change the count filter. To view the top baby names for a specific gender, change the gender filter. Adjusting the filters determines how many names will appear in the chart. 

Filtering by a count that is too high or too low, may produce unexpected results.  


For more information, go to http://www.health.ny.gov/statistics/vital_statistics/, or go to the "About" tab.

datasets.name: Baby Names
datasets.description:
New York State Baby names are aggregated and displayed by the year, county or borough where the mother resided as stated on a New York State or New York City (NYC) birth certificate.

The frequency of the Baby Name is listed, if there are: 5 or more of the same baby name in a county outside of  NYC; or 10 or more of the same baby name in a NYC borough.

For more information, check out http://www.health.ny.gov/statistics/vital_statistics/, or go to the "About" tab.

datasets.name: Baby Names: Trending by Name
datasets.description:
The column chart shows counts of baby first names by year over time. This chart can be filtered by year, gender, name, or count by changing these options under the Filter tab.  The default filter settings only show names with greater than 919 occurrences. To view the whole dataset, remove the count filter by clicking on the count box to uncheck the box. 

Filtering by a count that is too high or too low, may produce unexpected results.  


For more information, go to http://www.health.ny.gov/statistics/vital_statistics/, or go to the "About" tab.
